en_536273_0	The Supreme Court has rejected an appeals petition submitted by the Ven.
en_536273_1	Galagoda Aththe Gnanasara Thera on his sentencing to imprisonment.
en_536273_2	The petition filed by the Ven.
en_536273_3	Galadgoda Atthe Gnanasara Thera who has been sentenced to imprisonment for contempt of court was dismissed without being taken up for consideration.
en_536273_4	The decision was taken through a majority of three member panel of Supreme Court judges.
en_536273_5	An inquiry has been made whether he could be enlarged on bail until a ruling on the petition is given.
en_536273_6	The Ven.
en_536273_7	Gnanasara Thera was found guilty of contempt of court due to his misbehavior in the presence of the Homagama Magistrate on January 25th 2016.
en_536273_8	Accordingly he was sentenced to 19 years rigorous imprisonment to be served in six years.
